It's perplexing how four ingredients can pop out of my oven cookie-shaped and delicious. I've made them twice in a row in the unbearable heat, and I don't even like PB to start with. They're like a dream come true: one bowl, ridiculously quick/foolproof, and easily manipulable. I halved the sugar 'cause otherwise it'd be nauseatingly sweet, added a dash of vanilla + a dash of almond (it makes it 2x better), 2 T brown rice flour, and a bit of salt. If you're lazy like me, you can eyeball all the ingredients. With that said, too much PB makes it spread, but if you use an airbake sheet, too much PB will make it divinely crispy on the outside and chewy on the inside after 12 mins.

