Rating: 4
I have made these cookies twice now and they are great! How can you go wrong with only four ingredients? I did not grease the baking sheet and used either a silpat or parchment paper. I found that the parchment paper was too non-stick and the cookies would stick to the fork when I was flattening them out. The silpat worked better for flattening, but ultimately both parchment and silpat baked the cookies the same. I also found using a large fork, such as a serving fork, worked better then forks with small tines as the cookies stuck to the forks with small tines. Immediately after the cookies came out of the oven I placed a large Ghirardelli chocolate chip in the middle. EVERYONE loved them, especially my gluten intolerant coworker. I have tried other peanut cookie recipes that have been okay. What I like about this recipe really is that it gives you a really peanutty flavor!

