Okay -- I've made this cookie recipe at least a dozen times. I use whatever peanut butter I have around -- usually Skippy or Jif creamy -- and regular sugar. I haven't experienced any of the "graininess" issues other reviewers have. I think one of the keys to success in this recipe is to really cream the peanut butter and sugar together in the mixer for a good long time -- I'm talking at least 1.5 minutes. If I'm not adding anything special (peanut butter chips, mini chocolate chips, etc.), I do the traditional "fork squash" methon to get the familiar peanut butter cookie grid. Oh -- I also love using a Silpat with this recipe. I let the cookies sit on the sheet for 2 minutes before removing them to a wire rack. Everyone I've ever shared these with have loved these cookies!

