Is there ANYTHING more to say? 1.) TOO SWEET?: I've found that cheap store-brands of pb do fine, but that the sweetness varies widely by the amount of sugar in the pb, and the intensity/ domininance of the peanut flavor. 2.) ADD-INS TO TRY: I added freshly grated ginger to the dough a couple of times for a nice effect. Plan to try orange zest, &/or cinnamon. As far as "toppers", you can easily experiment with 2-3 cookies without committing the whole batch, using a "thumbprint" cavity!: I've added small cubes of sharp cheddar to some (good!), pecan halves (pretty good if your pecans are good to begin with), red cinn. hearts (okay), jam (okay). Press sprinkles of the decorating (?)pariels before baking (tiny, colored, candy balls) for added appeal to kids! 3.)A woman who makes this for our local farmers' market says the extra crunchy pb is too dry and crumbley, and the reduced fat pb's had not been satisfactory either.

